(916, '65d44badb0202', 'Investigating Standard Tests Usefulness In Diagnosing Silent Myocardial Ischemia, Alone Or In Combination in diabetic patients type 2', '2024-02-20 07:00:23', '', 1, 'Background: Despite the recognition of Silent Myocardial Ischemia (SMI) as a unique clinical condition, there is still substantial debate on the implementation of suitable screening protocols for individuals who are at high risk but are symptoms free.\r\nAim of study: to examine effectiveness of already used medical diagnostics in identifying SMI in diabetic individuals. \r\nPatients and methods: A case-control research included 50 type 2 DM patients and a control group of 100 healthy volunteers. All participants were investigated using: exercise treadmill test, 24-hour Holter Monitoring, Echocardiography, ECG, lipid profile, HbA1c, renal function test and full blood image.\r\nResults:  The use of tests combination is better than using one test alone in SMI diagnosis. Concordance between TMT and Holter is the highest in comparison to other combinations of tests. \r\nDiscussion:   It is clear from this analysis that TMT has the greatest role when combined with another test in detection of SMI in diabetic, while echocardiography has the weakest role in this regard.\r\nThus, the most beneficial test combination that was revealed in this study is the one that combine TMT with Holter monitoring test. \r\nThe second beneficial test combination is the one that combine TMT with echocardiography.  \r\n', '', '', '', 417, 'SMI, DM, tread mill test, echocardiography, Holter', 0, 0, 0, '2024-02-20 07:00:23', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
