(923, '65e83d0715c0e', 'Deficiency of Magnesium in Diabetic Cataract patients ', '2024-03-06 09:59:26', '', 3, 'magnesium is play role for maintaining the functional and structural integrity of several necessary eye tissues . magnesium-insufficiency  states, ATPase dysfunctions that produce denaturation of crystalline which  cause of cataract , opacification   of lens, Cataracts are 3-4 times more common in adult diabetes mellitus patients comparison with  non-diabetes mellitus . The current study aims to determine the level of serum magnesium  in patient with diabetic cataract  to comparison  with control group As well as, To define cut off value of magnesium  in patient with diabetic cataract  . Serum of 100 subjects were enrolled currently (40 diabetic cataract patient and 60 control )  were included in a case –control study. The magnesium levels  was measured by colorimetric  ,Peripheral serum magnesium  levels was significantly decrease  in diabetic cataract  comparison  with healthy individuals Hence, this study calculated cut off value 55.1ng/mL of. Magnesium diabetic cataract comparison with control ,. therefore, magnesium levels was lower  in individuals with diabetic cataracts more than control ,also magnesium  has been successful in detecting diabetic  cataract in comparison with healthy.  ', '', '', '', 423, 'Diabetic Cataract(DC), ,Oxidative Stress(OS),Magnesium (MG) ,Standard Deviation (SD), Diabetic Mellitus (DM).', 0, 0, 0, '2024-03-06 09:59:26', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
