(926, '6608462beca2a', 'The association of Interferon-induced transmembrane protein 3 gene (IFITM3) rs12252 C Polymorphism and serum level of IFITM3 with COVID-19 outcome', '2024-03-30 17:12:50', '', 2, 'Background and aims: The global pandemic known as Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) has different fatality rate and clinical effects in different nations. Genetic polymorphism is one of the factors impacting COVID-19 outcome. Interferon-induced transmembrane protein 3 gene (IFITM3 ) is known to bridge innate and adaptive immune responses, and to play a critical role against viral infection. Variants of the IFITM3 gene have been linked to the clinical response to some viral infections. Many studies found the correlation between C Allele of IFITM3 (rs12252) SNP and COVID-19 outcome. Our goal was to investigate the correlation between such polymorphism and serum level with severity of COVID-19 infection Methods and results: A total of 150 COVID-19 patients (75 severe, 75 mild/moderate) were enrolled in molecular study. Real time-PCR method is used to analyze the genotyping of IFITM3 polymorphism. Elisa Method was used to measure the level of IFITM3 protein in serum. The frequency of CC allele of IFITM3 variant (rs12252 ) were significantly prevalent in severe patients compared with mild/moderate patients (p-value=0.03) .The serum level of IFITM3 protein was significantly higher in sever patients compared to mild/moderate patients (p-value<0.01) Conclusions: There is obvious association between C allele of IFITM3 (rs12252) and disease severity of COVID-19 patients. Elevated level of IFITM3 are associated with disease severity and increased with the aggravation of the disease and vice versa.', '', '', '', 428, '· IFITM3, rs12252 C, COVID-19, SARS-CoV-2 ', 0, 0, 0, '2024-03-30 17:12:50', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
