(929, '66096ca695079', 'Effect of eight weeks of two types of feeding on Lee index, triglyceride glucose index, and atherogenic index of plasma in rats', '2024-03-31 14:11:24', '', 1, 'Diseases like obesity, diabetes, and atherosclerosis and the interplay between diet content: fat, Protein, and the ordinary diet may affect our well-being. With knowledge about the types of tests and diagnosis ways, we can use some of the diagnosis indices strategies to identify obesity, dyslipidemia, and its associated health risks like the Lee index, triglyceride glucose index, and atherogenic index of plasma. \r\nThis study aimed to investigate the Effect of eight weeks of two types of feeding on the Lee index, triglyceride glucose index, and atherogenic index of plasma in rats\r\nThe study involved 36 rats, divided into two groups, one receiving the ordinary diet and another receiving the modified diet, the studied parameters were the Lee index, triglyceride glucose index, and atherogenic index. Lee index was dependent on weight, and length from nose to anus, triglyceride glucose index was dependent on triglyceride and glucose while the atherogenic index of plasma was dependent on Triglyceride and HDL all parameters were measured at 2 intervals (0, and 8) weeks. The study was done in Animal House at the College of Veterinary, University of Baghdad.\r\nThe results showed that the Lee index did not significantly increase with no differences between the two groups conversely triglyceride glucose index and atherogenic index of plasma increased significantly in the modified and ordinary groups within 8-week intervals \r\nIn conclusion, in the two groups, the triglyceride glucose index and atherogenic index of plasma were increased and the Lee index was the same after 8 weeks.\r\n', '', '', '', 432, 'Type of food, obesity, Atherosclerosis, diabetes, ', 0, 0, 0, '2024-03-31 14:11:24', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
