(943, '6631f4dc38a46', 'The Effect of Stress on Periodontium: An Empirical Study on Medical Students in Yemen', '2024-05-01 08:15:39', '', 1, 'Stress represents a significant concept that has the potential to impact both the psychological and physical well-being of an individual. Despite this, there remains ambiguity in the precise delineation of stress and its function as a catalyst, a consequence, or the intermediary mechanism between the two. A group of separate tissues, known as the periodontium, enclose and uphold the teeth in the mandibular and maxillary skeletal frameworks. The periodontium becomes inflamed as a result of periodontitis, which causes the surrounding tissues to deteriorate and lose their ability to support the teeth, ultimately causing tooth loss. Several studies were conducted to examine the impact of stress on periodontium, but this topic is still worth exploring. Consequently, this study aims to empirically study the effect of stress on periodontium. To do so, four phases, which are (1) factor identification, (2) participant selection, (3) data collection, and (4) data analysis, were followed to achieve the study aim. In particular, a survey approach was used to gather data using the questionnaire technique before and after the examination period. The present study utilized a random sample method to gather data from students in the Faculty of Medicine and Health Science, University of Science and Technology, Hadramout, Yemen. The findings validate a positive association between stress and periodontal disease, as indicated by the pre-examination testing.', '', '', '', 444, 'Stress, Periodontium, Empirical Study, Medical Students,', 0, 0, 0, '2024-05-01 08:15:39', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
