(990, '6685a2c643bb1', 'Differential Impact of Alcohol-Related and Non-Alcohol-Related Fatty Liver Disease on Metabolic and Inflammatory Biomarkers: A Comparative Study.', '2024-07-03 19:29:36', '', 1, 'Background:  Fatty liver disease (FLD), which encompasses a spectrum of liver conditions, including alcohol-related fatty liver disease (AFLD) and non-alcohol-related fatty liver disease (NAFLD), represents a burgeoning global health concern characterized by the accumulation of fat in the liver. The gold standard for diagnoses remains liver biopsy, but it is invasive, expensive, and carries risks of complications. Alternative imaging modalities and traditional liver function tests are inadequate for accurately diagnosing and staging FLD. In light of these challenges, there is a critical need for noninvasive biomarkers that can accurately diagnose, stage, and prognosticate FLD. \r\nObjectives: This study aims to evaluate the levels of petraxine-3 (PTX3) and triglyceride-glucose (TYG) index, then compare these markers between AFLD, NAFLD, and healthy controls with liver enzymes and assess the diagnostic utility of these markers in distinguishing between AFLD and enzymes. \r\nMethods: Case-control was conducted in the Digestive System and Liver Department of the Medical City in Baghdad, starting in November 2023 and ending at the end of January 2024. The study enrolled 124 participants: 20 with AFLD, 50 with NAFLD, and 54 healthy controls. Serum levels of alanine transaminase (ALT), γ-glutamyl transpeptidase (GGT), study PTX3 and TYG index, and various lipid profiles were measured. \r\nResults: The study reveals significant differences between AFLD and NAFLD in liver enzymes, PTX3, TYG index, and lipid profiles. \r\nElevated PTX3 and TYG indexes in AFLD indicate greater inflammation and lipid metabolism abnormalities, distinguishing it from NAFLD. \r\nConclusions: Biomarkers like GGT and high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL-C) effectively differentiate AFLD from NAFLD.\r\n', '', '', '', 474, 'PTX-3, TyG index, FLD, AFLD, NAFLD', 0, 0, 0, '2024-07-03 19:29:36', 0, 0, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0),
